	abstract = {The demand for natural language processing tools for low-resource languages, like Kannada, has increased dra-matically with the rise of regional language content on dig-ital platforms. This study proposes a unified framework for automatically classifying Kannada news articles into multiple classes using transformer-based and traditional embeddings. The study proposes a dual strategy classification pipeline that combines Transformer models such as MuRIL, IndicBERT, mBERT, XLM-RoBERTa, LaBSE, and DistilBERT with Deep Learning Classifiers like Bi-RNN, LSTM, Bi-LSTM, GRU, Bi-GRU with pretrained multilingual word embeddings. In parallel, zero-shot and few-shot classification capabilities of lightweight generative Large Language Models like Bloom-560m and Gemma 2b-it which are known to be better for Indian languages like Kannada, are evaluated to demonstrate their utility with fine-tuning. Standard metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score were used to assess the 11,045 articles in 10 categories that comprised the Kannada News Dataset. The results show that Transformer based models significantly outperformed traditional models with MuRIL delivering the best performance of achieving highest performance for both Deep Learning and Transformer model based approaches, with a maximum accuracy of 0.79 and macro F1-score of 0.77. This demonstrates that transformer based multilingual embeddings enable superior performance with respect to improve accuracy and robustness of Kannada news classification. In order to support scalable and accurate Kannada Natural Language Processing, the study demonstrates how Deep Learning, Transformer architectures and LLMs can be combined to improve low resource language processing. © 2025 IEEE.},
