	abstract = {This paper proposes a answer Sentence Selection algorithm (MHIADI) based on multi-head interactive attention dynamic Integration combined with the idea of integration and the related technologies of model-based transfer learning. In order to solve the problems of word embedding semantic relationship, noise interference information of irrelevant words, and the occurrence position of Q&A pairs. Firstly, the BERT model was used as a language model for pre-training to obtain the word vectors of questions and candidate answers. Then, the feature vectors of the question and the candidate answer were obtained by dynamically integrating the three interactive attention mechanisms listwise, K-max and K-threhold. Finally, the matching probability of the question and answer is obtained by training on the comparative-integrated network framework. In order to further improve the accuracy of Q&A matching, we train the MHIADI model on the source dataset QNLI through a model-based transfer learning strategy, and then train the target datasets WikiQA and TrecQA on this basis to obtain the final Q&A matching model. Experimental results on WikiQA and TrecQA datasets show that the proposed MHIADI method based on transfer learning strategy has better recommendation performance than the current mainstream methods.  © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).},
