	abstract = {Research on open-source large language model (LLM) Chinese content security situational awareness based on deep learning aims to build an efficient and accurate system to maintain the health and stability of cyberspace and protect users' rights and interests. In this study, deep learning technology, especially open-source LLM such as BERT (Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers), is used to capture language features and contextual information through large-scale corpus training to identify and monitor harmful information. A deep learning-based model is designed, which includes a word embedding layer, a self-attention mechanism layer, a feedforward neural network (FNN) layer, and a classification output layer, so as to realize enhanced understanding and accurate classification of Chinese content. The model has been tested on two public Chinese content security data sets, showing better performance than the baseline models, with significantly improved accuracy and F1 score. In addition, the role of key components in the model, especially the importance of self-attention mechanism and pre-training BERT word vector, is verified by ablation experiments. The model of this study not only improves the classification accuracy, but also shows the deep understanding and efficient processing ability of Chinese texts, which provides strong technical support for building a clear cyberspace. ©2025 IEEE.},
